So their layout is okay.  I had a delicious chicken plater with veggies and fried plantain. It was really tasty and fresh. The guys who work here are friendly as well, delivering great customer service. This includes a warm inviting place to eat. Next time I visit, I want to see how breakfast is like. 4.5 stars! Good food at a cheap price!! It's fast food thats already prepared but the entrees were still good. Place has several tables in the back of the little restaurant. But there's surprisingly no bathrooms. I walked to the hospital across the street to use the restroom lol. I came around 9pm on a Saturday and it was not busy.  Half a chicken with 2 side combo for less than $10!  The chicken was so moist and fall off the bone delicious. The spicy green sauce that they have on the tables is delicious as well. My fiance had the beans and the macaroni cheese side. The beans were OK. The Mac and cheese was OK as well. Nothing to rave about.  I had the grilled ribs with mashed potatoes and I believe sweet plantains. The sides were OK. Main complaint is that the sides aren't really hot enough. The grilled ribs were pretty moist and flavorful. I had a bit too much food and couldn't finish it.  The sausage was delicious. It was hot and flavorful and the skin is snappy, which I love.  Overall, I would recommend the chicken and sausage definitely. Followed by the ribs. The sides were OK.
